HEADWORD: anabiosis
<hw>anabiosis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>suspended animation in
organisms during periods of extreme drought from which they revive when
moisture returns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

